  <div><h3>Inline vs Block Elements</h3></p>
<p><b>Inline</b> elements are tags that create inline (within the text) formatting. </p>
<p>Examples include <b>b</b>, <b>em</b>, <b>br</b>,and <b>img</b>. Another tag that falls into this category is <b>span</b> which is a container tag.
<p><b>Block</b> elements are tags that create a virtual box around its contents. </p>
<p>Examples include <b>p</b> which creates a block around the paragraph contents. Like with the inline elements, block elements has its own container tag called <b>div</b>.
</p>
